[required] Title: Program Installs onto machine in Andrew Hill's Office
Description:
Hi,

I have two timetabling programs that need to be installed onto the machine
in my office. They haven't be re-installed since all PCs were wiped.

I have the actual email for the below (Options 2024) if you need and the
software "Timetabler" I have on a CD ROM in my office.

Many thanks,
Andrew








Dear Andrew,



Thank you for your order to Upgrade to *Options 2024**.*.. I am including
the download link below.

You can see the details of new features introduced this year here…...
https://www.timetabler.com/PDFs/OPT-2024-Appendix.pdf

*To download the latest version of **Options* *please follow stages A, B,
C :*

*A.*
For safety's sake (it's best to be paranoid!), take [or make sure that you
have] a *Backup* of your existing data, as described on page ix in the
Manual (and HelpMovie 9), and keep this Backup safe. You can check that
this Backup is good by using FileMenu->Verify.
To be doubly safe, make a second Backup, on a USB memorystick, and Verify
it.

*B.*
The 4 steps to download & install the Upgrade are shown at :
http://www.timetabler.com/Download-Instructions-OPT.html

Click with your mouse on the link *below* to start the download, and follow
the 4 steps.
On a broadband connection the download will take less than a minute.


https://www.timetabler.com/upgrades/OP6d--2024/Setup.EXE



Please note that you should install the new version to the same directory
as the previous version of *Options*.  By default this is at C:\OPTwin
If you install to a different directory, then use FileMenu -> OPT-Restore to
load in the data that you saved in part A.



*C**.*
When you start *Options*,
i) go to HelpMenu->About Options and check that it now shows *Options
2024*  and
also
ii) check that it shows your School Name correctly at the top of the screen.


------------------------------

D.



If you want to install on a *different* machine from the download machine,
then :



--at Step 1 of the 4 steps above, choose ‘Save’ instead of ‘Run’, and
select a folder to Save the download in,



--Click on the ’Open folder’ button or visit the location you saved the
download in,



--The downloaded file is called Setup.EXE …copy it to a transferable memory
device (eg. to a USB FlashDrive 'memorystick').

--Then take that device to the second machine, find the file named
Setup.EXE and just double-click on it to install the new version.
Please note that you should install the new version to the same directory
as the previous version of *Options*.  By default this is at C:\OPTwin
If you install to a different directory, then use FileMenu -> OPT-Restore to
load in the data that you saved in part A.
------------------------------

E.



For more information about the *new features*, see www.timetabler.com/new


For more information about the TOOLS on-line method, see
www.timetabler.com/TOOLS

For more information about the Help & Support we provide, see
www.timetabler.com/help





If you have any questions, please let us know.

Best Wishes,



*Janet Woodhouse*

Accounts Department

Hi Mike



When we last spoke, I found your database was in Full recovery mode, which
can cause the log file in the database to grow large quite quickly. I
changed the setting the shrunk the file, and that’s when we agreed that it
had probably improved.



However, I’ve just started checking some other things that we normally
check, and I’ve noticed that your server only has 6.9GB or memory, and
currently 5.6GB is in use.  I would normally check that sort of thing, but
I can’t see any notes previously about this.  This may be the cause of your
issue. We are generally recommending 16GB of memory on Infinity servers,
and our absolute minimum in the past has been 8GB, so I would recommend
that you add memory into that server as soon as you can, and then we review
again.



I think that would probably solve any issues you are having, as I can’t
currently see anything else that would cause this type of issue in your
Infinity system.



Kind regards



Diane

Hi both



Another Teams related homework issue; sorry. Same as a previous time: first time he went to look at the music homework it logged him in fine. He went back later to do it, at which point he was asked to put in his password … and then it didn’t log him in fine – it didn’t log him in at all, and we got the same old same old error message.



We’ve gone through the same rigmarole as always: clearing cookies, trying incognito browsers, trying different devices and different operating systems etc etc etc. I know all IT teams around the world work on the premise that the user is somehow doing something wrong, but I can assure you that we’re not. (I’m even a Microsoft Certified Educator, for my sins, so I know my way around their products, and know how to Google for work arounds, and for the sake of speeding up these exchanges I go back and re-do every suggestion I’ve been given.)



It keeps coming back to the same fundamental thing: Sam’s Teams account allows him to access material once, and then the password is not recognised again.



I’m sure you’re as frustrated at getting these emails as we are sending them, but given that this has happened three or four times now I think we’ve reached the stage where something more far-reaching than trying the same things over and over is required! Sorry



Ed

Good evening,

I have asked out tech team if they had any further suggestions which might help with the login challenges Sam is having.

These are the things they suggested trying:



Can you ask that they make sure when using Teams in a browser that there isn't another account signed into the browser, they could also do with checking to see which Microsoft account is signed into the device itself if it's a windows machine, this might perhaps be causing some issues.

They could also try using incognito/in-private browsing windows in their browser and see if that fixes the issue.



I know they may sound obvious but I know from using my own computers at home, sometimes once a Microsoft login is used on a machine, it sometimes gets stuck in the background and it is very difficult to entirely disconnect it!



I hope this is helpful.

Kind regards

Sarah

As discussed in The Bugle recently, there are some amazing pieces of
software available for free to boost creativity in the classroom and beyond.

First up is Adobe Express - see details below. You are invited to attend a
free online session to find out more, to be held on Wednesday 13 December

Learn how to improve creativity throughout the curriculum
View this email in your browser

<https://vitalyork.us14.list-manage.com/track/click?u=93f537103a764aa5898210075&id=1003d6ab04&e=f53516ddb2>
will delve into the many features of Adobe Express.

Don't miss the chance to unlock the full potential of creativity in
education!


*About Adobe Express*

Adobe Express for Education is free to UK schools. It is an online
creativity tool with features that can help schools improve creativity
throughout the curriculum.

Adobe Express accounts can be linked to your Microsoft 365 or Google
Workspace logins providing all staff and students with easy unlimited
access to a range of tools including a video editor, animation creator,
graphic editor, image library with over two million royalty free images, a
PDF editor (perfect for editing past exam papers) and even the ability to
use AI to generate any graphic that you specify.

To help schools get started with Adobe Express, Adobe partner with TA
Education to offer schools technical support, staff training and creativity
workshops for students, all at no cost to the school.

Hi both



Another Teams related homework issue; sorry. Same as a previous time: first time he went to look at the music homework it logged him in fine. He went back later to do it, at which point he was asked to put in his password … and then it didn’t log him in fine – it didn’t log him in at all, and we got the same old same old error message.



We’ve gone through the same rigmarole as always: clearing cookies, trying incognito browsers, trying different devices and different operating systems etc etc etc. I know all IT teams around the world work on the premise that the user is somehow doing something wrong, but I can assure you that we’re not. (I’m even a Microsoft Certified Educator, for my sins, so I know my way around their products, and know how to Google for work arounds, and for the sake of speeding up these exchanges I go back and re-do every suggestion I’ve been given.)



It keeps coming back to the same fundamental thing: Sam’s Teams account allows him to access material once, and then the password is not recognised again.



I’m sure you’re as frustrated at getting these emails as we are sending them, but given that this has happened three or four times now I think we’ve reached the stage where something more far-reaching than trying the same things over and over is required! Sorry



Ed

Good evening,

I have asked out tech team if they had any further suggestions which might help with the login challenges Sam is having.

These are the things they suggested trying:



Can you ask that they make sure when using Teams in a browser that there isn't another account signed into the browser, they could also do with checking to see which Microsoft account is signed into the device itself if it's a windows machine, this might perhaps be causing some issues.

They could also try using incognito/in-private browsing windows in their browser and see if that fixes the issue.



I know they may sound obvious but I know from using my own computers at home, sometimes once a Microsoft login is used on a machine, it sometimes gets stuck in the background and it is very difficult to entirely disconnect it!



I hope this is helpful.

Kind regards

Resolution:
## Static Variables
# Installed Python Location
$PythonInstalledLocation = "C:\Program Files\Python312\python.exe"

# Set Python Install Command
$PythonInstallCommand = ".\python-3.12.1-amd64.exe /quiet InstallAllUsers=1"

## Script

# Check if python is already installed

if (Test-Path -Path $PythonInstalledLocation -PathType Leaf) {
    Write-Host "Python is already installed"

    # exit script with Error Code 0 Success
    exit
}

Write-Host "Installing Python"

# Install Python
Invoke-Expression $PythonInstallCommand

# wait 120 seconds after Installing Python, before checiking if installed!  (This is to allow the Python installer to finish)
Start-Sleep -Seconds 120

Write-Host "Check If Python has been installed Succesfully!"

if (Test-Path -Path $PythonInstalledLocation -PathType Leaf) {
    Write-Host "Python has been installed"

    # exit script with Error Code 0 Success
    exit
}

Write-Host "Python Failed to Install"

# Exit Script with Error Code 2 Failure
Exit 2

support your school by providing a FREE Adobe Express workshop, please
follow the link here: https://ta.education/creativity/

process with Adobe Express.

The easiest way to do secure printing is private print which can be set as
per below.



It is a driver setting to be done on printing preferences on the shared
print queue on the server.











Once the above is done, only the users that sent the job will be able to
retrieve with the code they chose.



Nothing to be done in the settings on the copier, just the above driver
setup.











Alternative to private print, are custom boxes by user or by department,
for which you require to create all the desired ones and then select in the
driver Custom Box instead of Private print.

support.

Morning,

We seem to have an issue with SIMS whereby for dual reg main pupils, if we
enter a D for attendance it is not registering it in the background of
SIMs, e.g. Sadie Hunter attending Manor 5 days a week should be getting
100% a week but it’s registering it at 0 which affects our figures.

Please could someone look into this?

Thank you,

Zara

To: IT Support Account <itsupport@voy.hslt.academy>
Cc: S Stancliffe <s.stancliffe@voy.hslt.academy>
Resolution:
If the student only has 'Attendance Not Required' codes during the date range of the report, it is expected functionality for the students to have 0% attendance, due to the reduced amount of possible sessions.
 
Note that this 0% will not affect the school's overall percentage attendance because the student has 0 possible sessions and so does not contribute to the school's overall possible session figure.

However, this does seem like student has not been there, when they actually have (but just had 'Attendance Not Required' codes in place (D, X etc.)).

The change to have students that have 'Attendance Not Required' codes and 0% attendance removed from reports entirely in a future release is to be discussed.

Hi there,

[https://apps.avid.com/kb/img/email_spacer.gif]
Discussion Thread
________________________________

Current Response:

Entered on: 11/6/2023 7:13 AM  Entered by: Alexis

Hi Huntington,

Thank you for contacting Sibelius Technical Support.
Please follow the instructions below to reset your Sibelius Preferences.
Please be warned that if you have preferences set up in Sibelius, they will be deleted.

WINDOWS:

- exit Sibelius
- click Start menu (for Windows 8/10/11, press window key then type Run, select Run)
- on search bar, type %appdata%
- click "Roaming" folder or press Enter
- inside the Roaming folder, go to Avid > Sibelius
- delete the "Playback Configurations" folder, "PlogueEngine" folder, and the PlaybackConfig.xml file
- empty Recycle Bin
- restart computer

MAC:

- quit Sibelius
- open Finder then select Go > Go to folder (keyboard shortcut: Command-Shift-G) (⌘⇧G)
- type ~/Library/Application Support/Avid/Sibelius
- drag the "Playback Configurations" folder, "PlogueEngine" folder, and the PlaybackConfig.xml file to trash
- next, go to ~/Library/Application Support/Avid/Common
- delete contents in the Common folder (if there are any)
- now go to ~/Library/Preferences
- look for a file called "com.avid.sibelius.plist"
- throw it in the trash
- empty Trash
- restart computer

Please let me know how it goes.


Best Regards,
Alex

Morning Adrian,



Following on from our conversation regarding external users including governors access to the school's system. We don’t recommend using Remote Desktops. We do recommend using Office 365 Shared Drivers or Google Team Drives which is what we do with other Schools & MATs we work with.



We have started looking at an alternative solution which has been highly recommended called Foldr<foldr.io> . The software has a feature called “School Governor packs” which simplifies sharing data with Governors, The software grants secure access to folders stored on the network or even in the cloud such as OneDrive.
